The paper discusses the application of deep learning in bioinformatics and biomedicine, which falls under the intersection of computer science and life sciences. The most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper specifically focuses on the use of deep learning methods. The second most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as deep learning is a subfield of AI. The paper also touches upon topics related to quantitative biology, such as data acquisition and knowledge discovery, which could fall under q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods) and q-bio.GN (Genomics). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of deep learning on healthcare, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
